WEBVTT

00:01.506 --> 00:04.790
You are listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

00:05.290 --> 00:14.321
For more information about First Baptist, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWN.org.

00:14.341 --> 00:18.546
Today's message comes from Senior Pastor, Dr. Bob McCartney.

00:18.566 --> 00:25.394
Well, good morning again and welcome to this final installment in this sermon series that we have called Storm Warning.

00:25.858 --> 00:43.799
And we're going to take a look this morning at Matthew chapter 25 verse 31 and following, which is the conclusion of what we call the Olivet Discourse, Jesus on the Mount of Olive speaking to His disciples about what will be the signs of the end of the age.

00:44.600 --> 00:53.490
And so Jesus comes to the conclusion of His remarks and this teaching in this particular section of Scripture in June of this year,

00:53.634 --> 00:59.580
There was a news story that was spread on several media outlets, about a 15 year old California teenage boy.

01:00.301 --> 01:09.290
And he had gone out sort of with his dogs and his two dogs in a new area where he had just moved, his two dogs disappeared.

01:10.111 --> 01:20.882
And as he searched for them, and he could hear them barking, but he couldn't find them, what he discovered is that they had gone into an old abandoned mine shaft and fallen about 20 feet.

01:21.282 --> 01:26.248
Well, he decided to climb down and rescue his dogs, but in so doing he found himself trapped.

01:26.288 --> 01:31.875
And so now he's in the bottom of the mine shaft, about 25 or 30 feet down.

01:32.416 --> 01:36.321
His dogs are down there with him and it's concrete walls straight up.

01:36.681 --> 01:38.183
He could not find a way out.

01:38.203 --> 01:46.994
And so he began to shout for help and eventually someone heard him and came looking for him, but it was no easy task to get him out because

01:47.106 --> 02:01.235
The man-shaft was old, it was decrepit, it's falling apart, and a rescue squad had to come in and a rescuer descend down with a rope-repell device in order to get him and the two dogs out.

02:01.255 --> 02:03.119
They did rescue the two dogs as well.

02:03.720 --> 02:08.530
But that story of descent and rescue is the story of humanity.

02:09.218 --> 02:13.203
that we are trapped and hopeless unless someone comes to rescue us.

02:13.263 --> 02:14.985
And that is what Jesus did for us.

02:15.045 --> 02:24.197
He descended to earth on a rescue mission so that he might take us out of our terrible predicament to be with him forever.

02:24.698 --> 02:25.719
But how does that happen?

02:25.779 --> 02:26.620
How does that occur?

02:26.660 --> 02:37.714
Well, we're going to see that here in Matthew chapter 25 verse 31 and following as we look at this passage of scripture about

02:38.018 --> 02:39.720
the end of time.

02:40.441 --> 02:50.593
You cannot really be comprehensive in a message series about end times unless you deal with the end of time.

02:51.515 --> 03:07.474
How does this thing end after all of the supernatural signs that we read about in the Revelation, after all of the events that Jesus has unfolded for us in Matthew 24, especially in here in chapter 25, how does it culminate?

03:08.002 --> 03:10.906
Well, that's what Jesus is going to deal with in this passage.

03:10.946 --> 03:21.440
And what you're going to see here is something that is totally contrary to what you will hear about Jesus in the media, in common culture today.

03:21.460 --> 03:27.668
It's totally opposite of what you will hear about about Jesus in progressive Christianity.

03:28.649 --> 03:32.434
What you're going to see today is not the Jesus who is inclusive.

03:33.026 --> 03:36.189
You're not gonna see the Jesus who just brings everybody together.

03:36.229 --> 03:37.690
Jesus is the great unifier.

03:37.730 --> 03:39.172
He's gonna bring everybody together.

03:40.033 --> 03:41.414
No, that's not what you're going to see.

03:42.575 --> 03:45.017
What you're going to see today is something that is uncomfortable.

03:45.918 --> 03:50.182
It is an uncomfortable, but it is a necessary truth.

03:51.283 --> 03:54.466
Jesus is divisive.

03:55.827 --> 03:59.030
Now, wait a minute, Bob, I didn't think that was right about Jesus.

03:59.671 --> 04:02.994
Well, let's listen to what the passage has to say to us

04:03.170 --> 04:05.753
And then you decide.

04:06.834 --> 04:11.019
Here's what the Bible says in Matthew 25 verse 31.

04:12.360 --> 04:31.762
But when the son of man comes in his glory and all the angels with him, then he will sit on his glorious throne and all the nations will be gathered before him and he will separate them from one another.

04:32.034 --> 04:43.285
Just as a shepherd separates the sheep from the goats and he will put the sheep on his right, but the goats on his left.

04:44.386 --> 04:53.834
Then the king will say to those on his right, come, you are blessed of my father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world.

04:54.115 --> 04:56.237
For I was hungry and you gave me something to eat.

04:56.297 --> 04:58.699
I was thirsty and you gave me something to drink.

04:59.299 --> 05:02.002
I was a stranger and you invited me in.

05:02.082 --> 05:03.404
naked and you clothed me.

05:03.784 --> 05:05.807
I was sick and you visited me.

05:05.927 --> 05:07.809
I was a prisoner and you came to me.

05:08.770 --> 05:16.620
Then the righteous will answer him, Lord, when did we see you hungry and feed you or thirsty and give you something to drink?

05:17.501 --> 05:21.826
And when did we see you as a stranger and invite you in or naked and clothed you?

05:22.327 --> 05:25.110
And when did we see you sick or in prison and come to you?

05:26.071 --> 05:31.538
And the king will answer and say to them, truly I say to you,

05:32.034 --> 05:41.868
to the extent that you did it for one of the least of these brothers and sisters of mine, you did it for me.

05:41.908 --> 05:49.359
Then he will say to those on his left, depart from me.

05:49.419 --> 05:59.474
You accursed people into the eternal fire which has been prepared for the devil and his angels, for I was hungry,

05:59.746 --> 06:01.388
and you gave me nothing to eat.

06:01.529 --> 06:04.052
I was thirsty and you gave me nothing to drink.

06:04.193 --> 06:07.097
I was a stranger and you did not invite me in.

06:07.157 --> 06:12.785
Naked and you did not clothe me sick and in prison and you did not visit me.

06:13.687 --> 06:23.281
Then they themselves will answer, Lord, when did we see you hungry or thirsty or as a stranger or naked or sick or in prison and did not care of you?

06:23.321 --> 06:26.025
Then he will answer them.

06:26.045 --> 06:29.330
Truly, I say to you,

06:29.666 --> 06:36.697
To the extent you did not do it for one of the least of these, you did not do it for me either.

06:37.738 --> 06:46.852
These will go away into eternal punishment, but the righteous into eternal life.

06:48.214 --> 06:52.660
This is how the story ends.

06:53.862 --> 06:55.244
I don't mean this story.

06:56.226 --> 06:59.090
I mean your story and

06:59.362 --> 07:00.223
history.

07:01.104 --> 07:03.406
That's the way it's all going to end.

07:03.867 --> 07:08.772
There is going to be a division of humanity.

07:09.333 --> 07:12.176
So let's explore what this text teaches us.

07:12.656 --> 07:16.541
First of all, there is the return of the king.

07:16.561 --> 07:19.104
There's the return of the king.

07:19.144 --> 07:28.754
And Jesus in this passage is giving us something of a summation of the way history is going to come to a conclusion.

07:29.186 --> 07:35.192
Now, many people have tried to shoehorn, well, which appearance of Jesus is this and when does this happen?

07:35.813 --> 07:37.615
That's not really what Jesus is doing.

07:37.635 --> 07:39.597
He's not giving us a chronology.

07:39.617 --> 07:43.261
He's not filling in a point on your chart.

07:43.281 --> 07:48.387
He's saying, here is the general sense in which this ends.

07:49.007 --> 07:59.058
It's a summation statement of history and it is a picture of might and grandeur of glory and of power.

07:59.618 --> 08:03.364
that Jesus says that he's going to come in his glory.

08:03.965 --> 08:11.376
All of the angels are going to be with him and he is going to sit on his glorious throne.

08:12.618 --> 08:28.402
And as he sits on that glorious throne, what we are going to see is a public universal cosmic demonstration of God's mercy and God's justice.

08:29.026 --> 08:32.249
They will both be demonstrated in that moment.

08:33.190 --> 08:35.212
And Jesus then gives a picture.

08:35.232 --> 08:36.914
Now some people have called this a parable.

08:37.034 --> 08:39.717
It's less a parable and more a metaphor.

08:40.517 --> 08:44.681
And he says that he's going to separate all humanity.

08:44.742 --> 08:47.765
He's going to divide all humanity.

08:48.725 --> 08:54.131
And he's going to divide them like a shepherd divides sheep and goats.

08:55.432 --> 08:57.394
Many times in the ancient world,

08:57.826 --> 09:03.594
Shepherds would have flocks that included both goats and sheep.

09:04.475 --> 09:07.199
And they would graze together during the day.

09:07.299 --> 09:11.004
They would take them out and they would find water and they would find pasture.

09:11.645 --> 09:16.012
And it was just a matter of convenience that they would graze them together.

09:16.252 --> 09:20.658
But when a shepherd would bring the sheep in at dusk,

09:21.698 --> 09:24.922
They would always separate the sheep and the goats.

09:24.962 --> 09:30.408
When they would put the sheep into the sheep fold, they would put the goats into a separate pen.

09:30.448 --> 09:32.891
There's a reason for that.

09:32.911 --> 09:36.055
Sheep are by nature, docile creatures.

09:36.155 --> 09:37.537
They're not aggressive.

09:37.637 --> 09:48.690
They have no God, when God created sheep, He gave them no natural defense mechanism, unlike most of the other animals in the animal kingdom.

09:49.922 --> 09:56.372
goats on the other hand are by nature aggressive and they're temperamental.

09:57.554 --> 10:06.227
And if you mingle the goats and the sheep, sometimes without the supervision of a shepherd, the goats will harm, sometimes even kill the sheep.

10:07.068 --> 10:12.837
And so a good shepherd would always separate the sheep and the goats at night.

10:14.019 --> 10:18.866
And when Jesus gives this picture, well, it was just an obvious metaphor for

10:19.202 --> 10:20.584
the people who were listening to it.

10:20.624 --> 10:23.508
They didn't have any trouble understanding it at all.

10:23.528 --> 10:30.597
It would be absolutely obvious, but Jesus says he's going to separate the sheep from the goats.

10:31.258 --> 10:34.182
He's going to put the sheep on his right hand.

10:35.003 --> 10:42.333
He's going to put the goats on his left hand and then he's going to address both of them.

10:43.415 --> 10:48.722
But here's the real issue for us, which pin

10:49.186 --> 10:49.967
are you in?

10:50.027 --> 10:54.153
That's the real question for all of us.

10:55.094 --> 10:59.641
Which pen are you going to be placed in at the end of time?

11:00.061 --> 11:03.726
Are you prepared for the return of Christ?

11:05.128 --> 11:09.895
Because in this moment, there's not going to be an opportunity to switch pens.

11:11.096 --> 11:15.122
The day of salvation is over, the doorway

11:15.202 --> 11:20.348
eternal life and grace has been closed in this moment that Jesus is describing.

11:21.409 --> 11:24.412
Are you prepared for this moment?

11:25.693 --> 11:29.057
If you were to ask me the question, Bob, what's the Bible out?

11:29.197 --> 11:29.978
Bible all about it.

11:29.998 --> 11:31.139
I would tell you it's all about this.

11:32.741 --> 11:40.850
The point of Scripture is to get us to this moment to understand that there is an eternity that is real.

11:41.410 --> 11:49.302
that there is more than the life that we live on this planet in the flesh, that there is something beyond this.

11:49.763 --> 11:58.176
And every person on planet earth is going to exist in one of these two pens forever, forever.

11:59.478 --> 12:03.545
So are you prepared for this moment?

12:03.565 --> 12:07.090
Because Jesus could return at any moment.

12:08.226 --> 12:12.793
I was a boy scout growing up and the motto of the boy scouts was be prepared.

12:14.315 --> 12:15.076
Are you prepared?

12:16.038 --> 12:17.139
I don't mean as a boy scout.

12:17.280 --> 12:18.942
I mean, are you prepared for eternity?

12:19.843 --> 12:28.517
My wife and I have had the occasion to meet over the past couple of years, a couple of really interesting men.

12:29.698 --> 12:34.085
And one of them, both of them actually were Olympic swimmers.

12:34.145 --> 12:37.490
We met them through my daughter's hobby and sport.

12:37.730 --> 12:38.471
She's a swimmer.

12:39.512 --> 12:41.654
And the father's name is Gary Hall.

12:41.734 --> 12:44.477
He swam on the same Olympics with a guy named Mark Spitz.

12:44.537 --> 12:46.158
Some of you will recall from 1972.

12:47.760 --> 12:52.545
And he actually won several medals during those Olympics, but Mark Spitz just outshined everybody.

12:53.245 --> 13:04.196
But his son, Gary Hall Jr. swam in the 1996 Olympics in Atlanta in 2000 in Sydney, won several gold medals and several silver medals.

13:04.817 --> 13:05.938
He lived

13:06.114 --> 13:11.945
until January of this year in the Palisades area of Los Angeles.

13:12.306 --> 13:18.618
And I say he lived there because his house was one of those houses that burned to the ground.

13:18.758 --> 13:23.046
Nothing was left but a foundation when it was all over.

13:23.667 --> 13:27.314
And we got to talk to Gary Hall Jr. this summer for a few minutes.

13:27.426 --> 13:34.913
and told him we had prayed for him and we had actually contributed to a go fund to me to try to help him out just a little bit because of what had happened to him.

13:35.474 --> 13:37.976
And he told us his story and it was incredible.

13:38.717 --> 13:44.282
He said, I just never thought the fire would get to my house where I was and where the fire was in the beginning.

13:44.343 --> 13:47.466
I just never thought it would get to my house.

13:48.366 --> 13:52.010
But the wind shifted just a little bit and it picked up just a little bit.

13:52.691 --> 13:56.114
And he said, I was not prepared.

13:56.770 --> 13:59.753
for how quickly that devastation would come.

14:00.774 --> 14:04.397
And as he drove out of his neighborhood, he got out of his neighborhood.

14:04.698 --> 14:09.302
He said it was like I was driving through a rain of fire.

14:09.362 --> 14:13.586
Those embers were just falling down on the street in front of him.

14:13.846 --> 14:17.970
And he got out with his life, but he lost every one of his Olympic medals.

14:18.291 --> 14:20.933
He lost some artwork that he had in his home.

14:21.194 --> 14:25.778
He lost some keepsakes that'll never be replaced in his life.

14:26.178 --> 14:27.539
but he got out with his own life.

14:27.559 --> 14:29.602
12 people didn't, though.

14:29.782 --> 14:35.708
12 people died in that fire because they were unprepared for what was coming.

14:36.549 --> 14:40.093
That's what Jesus says to us about this passage of Scripture.

14:40.393 --> 14:47.601
He says to us, you need to be prepared for eternity because there is coming a judgment.

14:49.183 --> 14:52.987
Secondly, Jesus says to us, there is a reward for the righteous.

14:54.128 --> 14:55.890
Now Jesus is going to turn

14:56.002 --> 14:56.983
to the two pins.

14:57.504 --> 15:00.648
First, he turns to the pin on his right hand.

15:01.208 --> 15:16.367
And to the pin on his right hand, the king will say to those on his right, come, you who are blessed of my Father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world.

15:17.368 --> 15:21.573
He says to those on his right hand, come, there is an invitation.

15:21.634 --> 15:25.298
He says, you are blessed of my Father.

15:25.378 --> 15:30.427
There are two words in the New Testament that are translated blessed.

15:31.469 --> 15:37.118
One is a rather general word for blessings, but the other is the word that is used here.

15:37.279 --> 15:40.024
It is the word eulogy.

15:40.484 --> 15:42.227
We get our word eulogy from it.

15:42.267 --> 15:48.318
And in the ancient world, a eulogy would always be delivered by a family member.

15:49.280 --> 15:50.642
And what he's saying is,

15:50.818 --> 15:55.024
that you have this blessing because you're a family member.

15:55.345 --> 16:05.520
And he even says our blessing is an inheritance from our father, inherit the kingdom prepared for you from the foundation of the world.

16:06.581 --> 16:16.777
Jesus says to those on his right, you are invited in, you are invited into what God has prepared for you.

16:17.758 --> 16:20.402
Now the sheep on the right hand,

16:21.218 --> 16:24.342
They're a little surprised, but if you read the passage, it's interesting.

16:24.362 --> 16:33.374
They're a little surprised by this because Jesus says, when I was in prison, you visited me and when I was hungry, you fed me.

16:33.454 --> 16:39.222
And he goes through that whole list of things that they have done for him.

16:39.342 --> 16:42.386
And Lord, when did we see you hungry and feel you?

16:42.406 --> 16:44.068
When did we see you naked and clothed you?

16:44.088 --> 16:45.430
When did we see you in prison?

16:46.772 --> 16:48.434
They are surprised.

16:49.314 --> 16:55.381
Because what they did was not for a reward, it was motivated out of love.

16:57.423 --> 17:01.207
They didn't serve God to get a reward.

17:01.267 --> 17:04.590
They didn't serve God to earn His favor.

17:04.951 --> 17:07.213
They served God because they loved God.

17:08.555 --> 17:10.857
And that translated to them serving others.

17:11.858 --> 17:15.442
When some people look at this passage of Scripture, they see these

17:16.418 --> 17:20.845
these qualities as important parts of our faith.

17:20.925 --> 17:22.407
And I want to say this to you, they are.

17:23.509 --> 17:34.545
It is important that we feed the hungry and that we come alongside those who are strangers and that we clothe the naked and we visit the sick and we visit those who are in prison.

17:34.786 --> 17:36.648
Yes, those are important qualities.

17:38.211 --> 17:44.480
But what you need to understand is that the Bible doesn't teach that that earns you salvation.

17:44.500 --> 17:45.682
That's not what this is about.

17:46.402 --> 17:54.032
You see, what was happening was that because of what had happened in them, something was being expressed through them, and that is the love of God.

17:55.935 --> 18:04.927
Chef Jose Andres has an organization called World Kitchen Relief, and World Central Kitchen.

18:05.749 --> 18:15.602
And World Central Kitchen, through this chef who's very, very famous, he goes into disasters, he goes into war-torn areas, and the media has

18:15.938 --> 18:19.362
sort of portrayed him as a great hero for what he's doing.

18:19.762 --> 18:20.323
And he is.

18:20.383 --> 18:22.045
I mean, it's a wonderful thing that he does.

18:22.105 --> 18:25.229
He feeds thousands of people when he does this.

18:26.110 --> 18:36.923
But did you know that every time there's a disaster, there are these big feeding trucks that roll up that say, send relief or Texans on mission on the side of them.

18:37.784 --> 18:39.325
And you're giving supports that.

18:39.906 --> 18:43.250
And we feed thousands of people in those areas.

18:44.354 --> 18:48.401
Not only that, but some people would say, well, Bob, what is our church doing in regard to this?

18:48.441 --> 18:49.483
What do we do?

18:50.264 --> 19:00.521
Well, every single week, the people at Faith Mission and Faith Rescue are impacted because life groups from our church go and serve.

19:00.601 --> 19:06.431
And part of what you give to our church goes to help fund Faith Mission and Faith Refuge.

19:06.771 --> 19:10.898
We support our local food bank, Southern Grit, which is a

19:10.978 --> 19:22.332
a ministry to combat human trafficking straight street, which is a ministry at risk youth that might not come necessarily to our church, but we want to reach those young people for Christ.

19:22.392 --> 19:33.866
And the crisis pregnancy center, now known as the center, which gives young ladies an alternative if they're thinking about an abortion and gives them an alternative to seek life.

19:34.387 --> 19:36.850
And that's what we're doing for the least of these.

19:37.602 --> 19:42.890
And if you want to get involved with those organizations and through those ministries, I would encourage that.

19:43.811 --> 20:02.258
There are men in our church that go every, every week to the all red unit of the prison outside of our city and they teach Bible studies to inmates and they're Gideon's in our church that go into the county jail and their wives go into the county jail to minister to those who need to hear about the love and the grace of Jesus.

20:03.426 --> 20:06.010
And those are opportunities that you have before you.

20:06.070 --> 20:11.718
And those are ways in which our church is seeking to fulfill this, but I don't want you to be mistaken.

20:12.660 --> 20:16.385
This passage does not teach a works salvation.

20:16.986 --> 20:23.156
What it teaches is that good works flow out of our salvation.

20:24.418 --> 20:29.225
See, Jesus is the exclusive way to heaven.

20:29.826 --> 20:32.690
He is the exclusive way to heaven.

20:33.122 --> 20:37.147
In John chapter 14, 6, Jesus said, I am the way, the truth and the life.

20:37.828 --> 20:40.651
No one comes to the Father, but through me.

20:41.432 --> 20:52.106
In Acts chapter 4, verse 12, and there is salvation in no one else, for there is no other name unto heaven given among men by which we must be saved.

20:52.126 --> 20:56.091
Jesus is the exclusive way to heaven.

20:57.152 --> 21:01.778
And salvation is exclusively by grace through faith.

21:02.306 --> 21:06.990
Ephesians chapter two tells us, for by grace you have been saved through faith.

21:07.571 --> 21:14.437
And this not of your own doing, it is the gift of God, not a result of work so that anyone would boast.

21:15.338 --> 21:21.003
We're told that we are saved by grace through faith and by grace through faith alone.

21:21.464 --> 21:32.274
It is not a result of our works and it is not a result of our effort or earning, but grace and faith that saves.

21:32.546 --> 21:34.989
always produces good works.

21:35.670 --> 21:48.747
Ephesians chapter 2 verse 10, for we are His workmanship, created in Christ Jesus for good works, which God prepared beforehand that we should walk in them.

21:50.049 --> 21:52.092
You see, there's going to be a great separation.

21:53.013 --> 21:58.560
Adrian Rogers, one of my favorite preachers, used to say, Jesus divides men.

21:59.141 --> 22:00.082
You can love Him.

22:00.354 --> 22:04.220
or hate him, accept him or reject him, but you cannot ignore him.

22:04.640 --> 22:12.432
He will separate all humanity and there is no fence sitting when he comes.

22:13.854 --> 22:24.350
And so the question for us is this, has the grace that I say I've experienced and the faith that I have expressed for Jesus, has it changed me?

22:25.371 --> 22:29.938
Is there any fruit in my life that gives evidence

22:30.370 --> 22:32.754
to what I claim to believe.

22:32.774 --> 22:33.215
Is it there?

22:34.477 --> 22:46.258
Because the Bible would say to us that if there is no fruit of your salvation, then you'd better check to whether there is a root to your salvation.

22:46.466 --> 22:49.250
Has the grace of God changed your habits?

22:49.670 --> 22:51.993
Has the grace of God changed your home?

22:52.374 --> 23:00.685
Has the grace of God swept into your life and in any meaningful way made a change in your heart, actions and attitudes?

23:01.767 --> 23:04.210
That's what Jesus would call on us to evaluate today.

23:05.131 --> 23:10.098
And so that's what he says to those on his right hand, which is comforting.

23:11.042 --> 23:16.729
Our former pastor, Dr. Jeffress, I've been reading his book in preparation for some of these sermons, Perfect Ending.

23:17.209 --> 23:19.812
There's a great quote in Dr. Jeffress book about this.

23:20.413 --> 23:27.842
He says, Jesus is teaching that your treatment of others is the clearest reflection of your relationship with him.

23:30.265 --> 23:34.930
The way we treat others is the clearest reflection of our relationship with Jesus.

23:35.831 --> 23:38.034
But then there is this pen on the left.

23:39.170 --> 23:41.994
and Jesus then turns his attention to them.

23:42.735 --> 23:46.341
And he speaks about the rejection of the rebellious.

23:47.582 --> 24:02.284
In verse 41, he will also say to those on his lift, depart from me, you accursed people into the eternal fire which has been prepared for the devil and his angels.

24:04.127 --> 24:08.914
The invitation to the pen on the right to the sheep

24:09.250 --> 24:09.931
is come.

24:12.694 --> 24:16.379
The word to the pen on his left is depart.

24:17.700 --> 24:18.001
Go.

24:19.142 --> 24:26.211
Be sent away forever into the eternal fire.

24:26.932 --> 24:28.013
Now those aren't my words.

24:28.073 --> 24:29.455
Those are the words of Jesus.

24:30.796 --> 24:35.542
But he does say this, which was prepared for the devil and his angels.

24:36.864 --> 24:38.866
The interesting contrast here is this.

24:39.586 --> 24:48.014
that the kingdom was prepared from the foundation of the world for the sheep.

24:49.676 --> 24:53.840
But the fire was actually prepared for the devil and his angels.

24:55.041 --> 25:00.046
It was never God's heart to send anyone to hell.

25:00.066 --> 25:00.286
Never.

25:01.908 --> 25:06.032
That was prepared for the rebellious devil and his angels.

25:06.332 --> 25:07.954
And what we know about them is that

25:08.226 --> 25:09.407
Satan was an angel.

25:09.467 --> 25:10.588
He's a created being.

25:11.029 --> 25:12.510
He rebelled against God.

25:12.530 --> 25:15.053
And because of that, he was kicked out of heaven.

25:15.073 --> 25:16.855
He was kicked out of the presence of God.

25:17.435 --> 25:20.378
And someday he's going to be cast into a lake of fire.

25:20.438 --> 25:24.222
As a matter of fact, that's what the Bible says in Revelation 20 verse 10.

25:24.522 --> 25:30.909
And the devil who had deceived them was thrown into the lake of fire and sulfur where the beast and the false prophet were.

25:31.189 --> 25:35.033
And they will be tormented day and night forever and ever.

25:35.393 --> 25:36.274
Hallelujah.

25:39.010 --> 25:49.024
I yell at football games when my team scores, and I won't tell you my loudest yell is going to be reserved for when God kicks the devil into the lake of fire, I think.

25:49.044 --> 25:56.033
But this is a place of a literal, eternal, conscious torment.

25:58.196 --> 26:04.124
My friends, we don't talk about this enough, and I'm the preacher, so I'll put all that blame on me.

26:06.267 --> 26:08.690
But there are two destinations for eternity.

26:10.146 --> 26:12.368
heaven and hell.

26:14.210 --> 26:15.071
Who goes to hell?

26:16.692 --> 26:19.715
Well, Revelation 2015 answers that question quite clearly.

26:20.996 --> 26:32.006
And if anyone's name was not found written in the book of life, he was thrown into the lake of fire.

26:32.026 --> 26:40.114
If your name is not written in the Lamb's book of life, then my friend, I plead with you.

26:41.410 --> 26:42.311
to turn to Jesus.

26:43.552 --> 26:58.987
Every person who has trusted Jesus as Lord and Savior, who's trusted that His sacrifice on the cross was the full and sufficient payment for our sin, and who has believed in the resurrection, who's committed their life to Him.

26:59.407 --> 27:02.830
Every person's name is written in the Lamb's Book of Life.

27:03.471 --> 27:03.811
Everyone.

27:05.633 --> 27:07.055
And it will never be blotted out.

27:08.616 --> 27:10.738
But if your name is not written,

27:10.882 --> 27:12.464
in that book.

27:12.484 --> 27:22.777
If you've not trusted Jesus Christ as your Lord and Savior, if you've not committed your life to Him, then your name is not written in the book, and there will be no admittance into heaven.

27:23.679 --> 27:25.401
And here is the horrible truth.

27:26.522 --> 27:33.151
You will be cast into a place of everlasting, eternal, conscious punishment.

27:34.212 --> 27:36.435
Jesus told a story in Luke chapter 16.

27:37.697 --> 27:38.738
Luke chapter 16.

27:38.946 --> 27:40.969
He tells the story of a rich man and Lazarus.

27:41.610 --> 27:42.892
Some people call it a parable.

27:42.972 --> 27:44.254
Jesus didn't say it was a parable.

27:44.915 --> 27:46.117
The Bible doesn't say it's a parable.

27:46.317 --> 27:47.219
I think it's a true story.

27:48.881 --> 27:52.947
And this rich man is cast into a place of suffering.

27:53.668 --> 28:00.018
And what he says about the torment that he is experiencing, he says,

28:00.578 --> 28:10.087
He says, Father Abraham, have mercy on me and send Lazarus to dip the end of his finger in water and cool my tongue for I am in anguish in this flame.

28:11.749 --> 28:19.557
He fully knew where he was and he was experiencing the horrors of an eternity without God.

28:25.042 --> 28:29.266
This week, I had an encounter with a gentleman.

28:30.658 --> 28:36.307
who's come to our church and he told me something that I think is really frightening.

28:37.850 --> 28:42.217
He said, I grew up going to church, grew up going to worship services.

28:43.299 --> 28:45.583
I don't have to have a hymnal to sing the songs.

28:45.863 --> 28:47.205
I need those songs all my life.

28:48.407 --> 28:49.409
I've sung the songs.

28:50.791 --> 28:51.773
I've heard the sermons.

28:53.676 --> 28:57.362
I know the answers to the Sunday school questions.

28:59.234 --> 29:06.743
He said, I've even prayed a prayer before, but he's told me last Sunday when he left this church building.

29:08.305 --> 29:15.474
He said, if I would have left this place and I would have died, I'd spent an eternity separated from God.

29:15.614 --> 29:17.737
I'd go to hell.

29:17.757 --> 29:22.102
And he prayed to receive Christ this week, this week.

29:23.484 --> 29:28.370
And what I'm going to tell you is this, that there is a hell and it is real,

29:28.930 --> 29:30.192
And there is a danger.

29:31.274 --> 29:35.139
And that danger is a danger of a shallow confession.

29:35.881 --> 29:39.927
It is the danger of believing that you are saved by praying a prayer.

29:39.987 --> 29:41.129
I want you to understand something.

29:41.149 --> 29:43.713
You are not saved by praying a prayer.

29:45.595 --> 29:49.642
You are saved by totally trusting Jesus.

29:51.705 --> 29:57.714
It is faith that is the conduit for the grace that saves.

29:58.050 --> 30:21.618
Now, please understand, I think the best way to express that is in a prayer, but somewhere we got off track and we think that if you just said the words that you're saved and that is not true, where we have communicated that and maybe sometimes we didn't try and it was just misunderstood.

30:22.050 --> 30:25.174
But where we have communicated that, we are in error.

30:25.234 --> 30:29.860
Just repeating the words of a prayer never saved anyone.

30:32.263 --> 30:38.031
Unless that prayer is coupled with genuine faith.

30:39.413 --> 30:41.295
Number one, that you are a sinner.

30:42.657 --> 30:46.482
Number two, that Christ died for you on a cross.

30:46.882 --> 30:57.913
Number three, that his blood was the full payment for your sin and that he was literally and physically resurrected from the dead and he is alive today and able to save.

30:59.074 --> 31:03.999
If that's the Jesus you believe in, I don't want to cast any doubt on your salvation.

31:04.660 --> 31:06.002
You're as saved as I am.

31:06.202 --> 31:08.164
You're as saved as the Apostle Paul was.

31:09.986 --> 31:13.089
I don't want anybody to doubt their salvation.

31:13.109 --> 31:14.290
But if you thought

31:14.882 --> 31:22.494
that just saying the words somehow punched your ticket to heaven, you're as lost as a duck in the desert.

31:24.297 --> 31:30.547
And you wonder why you hear this stuff and it doesn't work for you.

31:31.369 --> 31:34.714
And you wonder why the Bible doesn't make any sense to you.

31:36.317 --> 31:37.218
I want to tell you why.

31:37.899 --> 31:40.904
You've had a false conversion experience.

31:41.004 --> 31:42.066
It's counterfeit.

31:42.338 --> 31:46.244
You were led astray and you need to trust Jesus today.

31:48.327 --> 31:51.612
See, that's the message of the end times.

31:52.714 --> 31:55.879
Trust in Jesus and it'll all work out.

31:57.982 --> 32:06.275
Don't get caught up in all your charts and graphs and when this is going to happen and who the Antichrist is and start trying to guess what day Jesus is coming back, you're not going to be able to do that.

32:08.078 --> 32:10.642
Trust in Jesus and you'll be fine.

32:12.386 --> 32:14.228
Make sure your family trust in Jesus.

32:14.288 --> 32:15.069
So they'll be fine.

32:16.030 --> 32:18.873
Make sure your neighbors trust in Jesus and tell them about him.

32:18.893 --> 32:19.674
So they'll be fine.

32:19.994 --> 32:23.959
Tell your enemies about Jesus so that they'll get saved and they'll be fine.

32:24.399 --> 32:25.901
And then maybe they won't be your enemies anymore.

32:28.904 --> 32:29.905
So how does this work?

32:31.167 --> 32:35.451
I wanna read you a passage of scripture and then I'm gonna be finished.

32:35.471 --> 32:38.034
But in 1 Corinthians chapter six, verse nine,

32:39.938 --> 32:43.903
The Apostle Paul writes a really sobering paragraph.

32:45.325 --> 32:50.873
Or do you not know that the unrighteous will not inherit the kingdom of God?

32:51.894 --> 32:54.237
Do not be deceived.

32:55.559 --> 33:06.834
Neither the sexually immoral, nor idolaters, nor adulterers, nor homosexuals, nor thieves, nor the greedy,

33:07.138 --> 33:14.890
Nor those habitually drunk, nor verbal abusers, nor swindlers, will inherit the kingdom of God."

33:16.071 --> 33:31.154
Now that's pretty specific, but listen to this last verse, and such were some of you, but you were washed

33:31.330 --> 33:32.672
You were sanctified.

33:32.972 --> 33:39.743
You were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ and in the spirit of our God.

33:41.986 --> 33:44.650
Heaven is not for perfect people.

33:45.171 --> 33:45.992
There aren't any of those.

33:47.394 --> 33:57.610
Heaven is for people who've been made perfect with the perfect righteousness of Christ, which has been imputed to them by faith.

33:59.192 --> 34:00.594
And such were some of you.

34:01.218 --> 34:11.031
but you were washed, you were sanctified, and you were justified in the name of the Lord Jesus Christ.

34:11.051 --> 34:14.336
You've been listening to a message from First Baptist Church, Wichita Falls.

34:14.916 --> 34:23.528
For more information about First Baptist, including gathering times and locations, click the link in the show notes or go to FBCWF.org.

34:23.928 --> 34:25.170
We'll see you next week.

